  "functions": {
    "domain::guard::policy::check_commands": {
      "action": "modify",
      "role": "FreeFunction",
      "params": [
        { "name": "commands", "ty": "&[SimpleCommand]" }
      ],
      "returns": "GuardVerdict",
      "is_async": false,
      "generics": [],
      "where_predicates": [],
      "docs": "Checks pre-parsed simple commands against the guard policy. Modified: (1) D3/IN-03: adds SOTP_GUARDED_GIT exact-match keyword scan over quote-stripped argv tokens (SimpleCommand.argv elements); the raw command string scan for the same keyword is performed by GuardHookHandler (usecase layer) before calling this function, since SimpleCommand does not carry the original raw string; (2) D4/IN-04: removes env unconditional block, command_contains_expansion, has_output_redirect blanket block, FILE_WRITE_COMMANDS (tee), and sed -i check. Retained: direct git subcommand checks, launcher stripping, is_bin_sotp_overwrite, and the new redirect-target test-file pattern check delegated to block-test-file-deletion (CN-07/IN-05).",
